Who we are looking for
We are looking for a Sales Representative based in Singapore within our Sector Solutions team reporting to the Head of Sector Solutions, Asia Pacific. You will have primary responsibility for growing State Street in the South East Asia region of Asia Pacific across its key client segments and meeting/exceeding given sales targets. This is a new business sales role, requiring you to research opportunities, initiate discussions, build prospect relationships, manage the sales process and close deals that generate new revenue. Primary prospects will be asset managers, asset owners, sovereign wealth clients and insurance companies

Why this role is important to us
The team you will be joining is a part of State Street Global Services (SSGS). SSGS gives asset owners and managers access to the essential financial tools they need to deliver effective investment solutions. From core custody, accounting, fund administration and shareholder recordkeeping, to complete operations solutions and servicing for alternative assets like OTC derivatives, private equity and real estate, SSGS’ tools help our clients make better investment choices and act on growth opportunities.
Join us if making your mark in the financial services industry from day one is a challenge you are up for.

What you will be responsible for
As Sales Representative you will

  Deliver/exceed annual sales and revenue targets by building and executing sales strategies
  Lead sales process from prospecting through close, including lead generation, client meetings, prospect qualification, and RFP completion
  Successfully partner with a virtual team of executives and subject matter experts through all aspects of a long and detailed sales cycle
  Proactively build/drive pipeline volume, accelerate sales cycle, actively manage to close
  Represent State Street at relevant industry events and conferences
  Develop and maintain strong product knowledge and understanding of competitive offerings
  Collaborate with relevant management resources to drive product and messaging strategies to differentiate our solutions
  Partner with Product Specialist and Demo team during client presentations to ensure client engagement and positive outcome

What we value
These skills will help you succeed in this role

  Leadership skills and proven sales success and track record
  Ability to gain access and interact with C-level executives
  Strong time management and presentation skills
  Strong written and verbal skills along with a high level of professionalism
  Demonstrated track record of achieving/exceeding financial goals
  Ability/process of accurate pipeline management from initial lead to close

Education &amp; Preferred Qualifications

  BA/BS degree, Masters degree (or equivalent) preferred
  10 - 12+ years successful sales experience
  Strong financial services background and experience

Additional requirements
Willingness for regular business travel